description:
Friction observed while working the kitty WindowServer/IOSurface leak (origin/main 533f513; alongside bd-b94fa1/bd-ad43f8).

Several pi-graphics/box-chrome tests assert against the extension SOURCE TEXT with literal pinned call-site strings, e.g.:
  assert.match(source, /buildDeleteByZIndexBandCommand\(\{ zIndices: PI_GRAPHICS_RESERVED_Z_INDICES \}\)/);
  assert.match(source, /buildScopedDeleteCommand\(\{ ownedImageIds: state\.ownedImageIds \}\)/);
  assert.match(source, /buildDeleteByZIndexBandCommand\(\{ zIndices: \[PI_GRAPHICS_Z\.BOX_CHROME\] \}\)/);

A benign call-site edit (adding a freeData:true argument) broke 4 of these literal matches in test/pi-graphics.test.js, forcing churn unrelated to behaviour. dev-0 hit the same brittleness in bd-b94fa1/bd-ad43f8 (updated test/pi-graphics.test.js, box-chrome.test.js, id-space tests).

Suggested fix-shape: prefer behavioural assertions (import the builder and assert the emitted escape contains a=d,d=I / d=Z, or assert the wired code path's OUTPUT) over regex-pinning the exact source call-site argument object. Where a source guard is genuinely wanted (e.g. "never global delete-all"), pin the minimal invariant token (deleteMode/d=A absence) not the full argument list. Reduces churn on every benign refactor of these call sites.

Filed via reflect-session mixin from the 2026-06-14 kitty-leak audit session (agnt-dev-1).

TRIAGE NOTE 2026-06-17 (ms-mac-agent-utils-agnt-dev-0, read-only assessment during idle): the 3 specific brittle pins cited above (buildDeleteByZIndexBandCommand({ zIndices: PI_GRAPHICS_RESERVED_Z_INDICES }), buildScopedDeleteCommand({ ownedImageIds: state.ownedImageIds }), buildDeleteByZIndexBandCommand({ zIndices: [PI_GRAPHICS_Z.BOX_CHROME] })) are NO LONGER PRESENT in test/pi-graphics.test.js (grep count 0) — already refactored away by bd-f4d277 (shared evictOwnedImage helper, landed 2026-06-16). The general friction remains valid (test/pi-graphics.test.js still has ~459 `assert.match(source, ...)` source-text pins) but the cited examples are stale (cross-ref bd-c9c0de re: stale reflect-session premises). Scope caution for whoever takes this: it is a large, judgment-heavy surface on a hot, frequently-reintegrated file — convert only the genuinely brittle full-argument-object pins to behavioural/minimal-invariant assertions incrementally; do not bulk-rewrite all 459. Not suitable for unprompted auto-claim; needs explicit operator/controller scoping.
